  id: External_layer_of_sheat_of_recti_abdominis
  partName: External layer of sheat of recti abdominis
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The external layer of the rectus abdominis sheath is a fibrous connective tissue
    structure encasing the rectus abdominis muscle along the ventral abdominal wall.
    Formed by aponeuroses of the external and internal abdominal oblique muscles,it
    provides structural support '
  - and maintains abdominal wall integrity. This sheath protects underlying musculature
    while facilitating force transmission during trunk flexion, respiration, and
    postural stabilization. Weakness or disruption can compromise abdominal wall
    strength, predisposing the animal to herniation or instability.
